<paragraph id="53708D06C4126A41ECC8882069AB4023" pageId="4" pageNumber="89">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF0A4CFCDDAC1DD67DD4BBF74DFDC93E" pageId="4" pageNumber="89">
<taxonomicName id="7E1A60B53EBBAF2ABD3695150BEE3A01" authorityName="M. A. Johnson" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyrtandra hispida" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="3E54BE8CEC44627590484E9ABED72130" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="89">Cyrtandra hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A4865869FEE74F016CA4AA56C5939EE7" genus="C." lsidName="C. waisaliensis" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="waisaliensis">C. waisaliensis</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but differs in its axillary cyme inflorescence of 2-4 flowers (vs. cauliflorous cyme inflorescence of 2-8 flowers), green bracts and bracteoles 5-9 mm long (vs. white bracts and bracteoles 3-10 mm long), calyx pale green and 29-31 mm long (vs. calyx white and 23-37 mm long), corolla tube 31-34 mm long (vs. corolla tube 23-27 mm long), and staminodes 2 (vs. staminodes 3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
